title: Japan’s H3 rocket launch fails after second stage malfunction
summary: Japan’s brand-new H3 rocket was destroyed on its March 7 inaugural flight after the vehicle’s second-stage engine failed to ignite.

title: Japan’s flagship H3 rocket fails on first test flight
summary: Japan’s first H3 rocket, designed to launch satellites and resupply space stations, fell back into the atmosphere Monday after its second stage engine failed to ignite five minutes into the new launcher’s inaugural test flight, destroying the rocket and a three-ton Earth observation spacecraft.

title: BREAKING! Japan's H3 Rocket Fails During Inaugural Launch
summary: Japan's H3 rocket fails after second stage doesnt ignite

title: Ukrainian government criticizes Vega C investigation
summary: The Ukrainian government claims that European investigators were “premature” in concluding that a component from a Ukrainian company was the blame for the failed Vega C launch last December.

title: Investors in space startups see hurdles in defense market
summary: In some sectors of the space industry, innovative technologies from startups don’t stand much of a chance to be part of a DoD program due to institutional and cultural barriers, said Jordan Noone, co-founder and general partner of Embedded Ventures.
